# ucl-tools (Python)

UCL Tools SDK for Python - Get and execute tools via REST API.

## Installation

```bash
pip install ucl-tools
```

## Usage

```python
from ucl_sdk import UCLClient

client = UCLClient(
    space_id="your-space-id",
    tenant_id="your-tenant-id",      # optional, defaults to ""
    gateway_id="your-gateway-id",    # optional, defaults to space_id
    api_key="your-api-key",          # either api_key or auth_token required
    # auth_token="your-auth-token",
)

# Get available tools
tools = client.get_tools(limit=10)
print(tools)

# Get tools filtered by prompt (search by keywords)
email_tools = client.get_tools(limit=10, prompt="send email")
print(email_tools)

# Execute a tool
result = client.execute_tool(
    tool_name="tool_name",
    parameters={
        "param1": "value1",
    },
)
print(result)
```

## API Reference

### `UCLClient`

#### Constructor Parameters

| Parameter | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `space_id` | `str` | Yes | - | Your space ID |
| `tenant_id` | `str` | No | `""` | Your tenant ID |
| `gateway_id` | `str` | No | `space_id` | Your gateway ID |
| `api_key` | `str` | No* | - | Your API key |
| `auth_token` | `str` | No* | - | Your auth token |

*Either `api_key` or `auth_token` is required.

#### Methods

##### `get_tools(limit: int = 10, prompt: Optional[str] = None) -> list[Tool]`

Retrieves available tools. Optionally filter by keywords in tool name or description.

```python
class Tool(TypedDict):
    name: str
    description: str
    inputSchema: dict[str, Any]
```

##### `execute_tool(tool_name: str, parameters: Optional[dict] = None) -> ExecuteToolResponse`

Executes a tool.

```python
class ExecuteToolResponse(TypedDict):
    body: dict[str, Any]
    rawBody: str
    statusCode: int
```

## Development

```bash
# Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

# Install in development mode
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# Run tests
pytest

# Run type checking
mypy ucl_sdk
```

